### What is Stainless Steel Double Curved Fabrication?

Stainless steel double curved fabrication refers to custom-formed metal structures that feature complex three-dimensional curved surfaces in multiple directions (both horizontal and vertical curvature).
Unlike flat or single-curved panels, double curved stainless steel products require advanced forming techniques and precise engineering.

They are widely used in high-end architectural facades, artistic installations, luxury interiors, and landmark projects, where fluid geometry and premium aesthetics are essential.

With processes such as CNC forming, segment welding, polishing, and PVD coating, double curved stainless steel delivers both structural strength and sculptural beauty.

### Specifications
Material: Stainless Steel (201 / 304 / 316)
Thickness: 0.8mm – 6.0mm (depending on structure)
Surface Finish: Mirror / Brushed / Hairline / Sandblasted / PVD Coating
Color: Silver / Gold / Rose Gold / Black / Bronze / Custom
Forming Method: CNC Bending / Rolling / Segment Welding
Structure: Single Layer / Reinforced Frame / Hollow Structure
Size: Fully Customizable
Tolerance: High-precision fabrication for complex geometry

